{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6dc69840-538b-4d63-8f86-6c78c1d6634b","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n1. **`PackAsTool`** — marks the project as a .NET tool.\n2. **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users run after installing.\n3. **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be console apps.\n\n### Publish workflow\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push (use your NuGet API key)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs the stdio MCP server\n```\n\nWant me to create or update your `.csproj` with these settings?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75462d8f-ec8b-40cf-af29-d6d14dfb6dd2","outputTokens":415,"requestId":"1587:2F39F8:32DAE93:378AAA3:69FBE67A"},"id":"f21dac47-26dd-4ced-a633-c323736a61ef","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:10:29.508Z","parentId":"9cbc7654-d2dd-4cd9-b6da-603541c337a5"}
